            <title>[CASSANDRA-16175] Avoid removing batch when it&apos;s not created during view replication</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16175</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When the base replica is also a view replica we don&apos;t write a local batchlog, but they are unnecessarily removed when the view write is successful, what creates (and persists) a tombstone into the system.batches table.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
